The paper deals with analyzing the representation of world literature in Wikipedia using data from DBpedia, which is a community project for extracting structured information from Wikipedia. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, information retrieval (IR), and computational linguistics (CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of intrinsic and extrinsic measures to evaluate the results, which falls under the category of cybernetics (CY) and social and information networks (SI). Overall, the paper's focus on digital analysis of Wikipedia data makes it most likely to belong to the categories of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
